🔧 Setup & Configuration
Command	Description
git config --global user.name "<Your GitHub Username>"	Set global username
git config --global user.email "<Your GitHub Email>"	Set global email address
git version	Show installed Git version

📁 Repository Initialization
Command	Description
git init	Initialize a local Git repository
git clone <repository-URL>	Copy remote repo to local machine

📤 Adding & Saving Changes
Command	Description
git add <filename>	Stage a specific file
git add .	Stage all changed files in the current directory
git add -A	Stage all changes in the entire repo
git commit -m "message"	Save staged changes with a message
git status	Show status of working directory and staging area
git log	View commit history
git diff	Show unstaged differences
git diff HEAD~1 HEAD	Show changes between last 2 commits
git diff <branch-1> <branch-2>	Compare two branches

🌿 Branching & Merging
Command	Description
git branch	List branches
git branch <new-branch>	Create a new branch
git branch -d <branch-name>	Delete a branch
git checkout <branch>	Switch to a branch
git checkout main	Switch to the main branch
git merge <branch-name>	Merge a branch into the current branch

🔄 Remote Repositories
Command	Description
git remote	List remote repositories
git remote -v	Show remotes with URLs
git remote add origin <URL>	Add a remote repository
git remote rename origin upstream	Rename remote repository
git remote rm <name>	Remove a remote

🌐 Fetching, Pulling & Pushing
Command	Description
git pull origin main	Fetch and merge changes from remote main
git push origin <branch>	Push current branch to remote repo

🧹 Undoing Changes
Command	Description
git reset	Unstage staged files
git reset --hard HEAD	Discard all uncommitted changes
git revert HEAD	Undo the last commit (creates a new commit)

📦 Patch & Email Workflow (Advanced)
Command	Description
git format-patch HEAD~3	Create patches for last 3 commits
git request-pull origin/main <branch>	Create email summary for pull request
git send-email *.patch	Email patches (requires configuration)
git am <patchfile.patch>	Apply a patch to the repo

🖥️ Serving & Viewing Repositories
Command	Description
git daemon --base-path=/path/to/repos	Start Git server with Git protocol
git instaweb --httpd=webrick	View repo in web browser instantly

🔁 Merge Conflict Help
Command	Description
git rerere	Reuse recorded conflict resolution
git config --global rerere.enabled true	Enable rerere feature

